people about, through the way of the wilderness of the Red sea: and the children of Israel went up harnessed out of the land of Egypt.","year":-1491},{"id":"rec2qqPDyNdFItZxY","ref":"Exod.13.19","text":"And Moses took the bones of Joseph with him: for he had straitly sworn the children of Israel, saying, God will surely visit you; and ye shall carry up my bones away hence with you.","year":-1491},{"id":"recr3oMDaICVPmgFZ","ref":"Exod.13.20","text":"And they took their journey from Succoth, and encamped in Etham, in the edge of the wilderness.","year":-1491},{"id":"recQQwbrq89AT68Ij","ref":"Exod.13.21","text":"And the LORD went before them by day in a pillar of a cloud, to lead them the way; and by night in a pillar of fire, to give them light; to go by day and night:","year":-1491},{"id":"recCwGG1a6H9huonJ","ref":"Exod.13.22","text":"He took not away the pillar of the cloud by day, nor the pillar of fire by night, from before the people.","year":-1491},{"id":"rechtJtrFYYnoTO1h","ref":"Exod.14.1","text":"And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,","year":-1491},{"id":"rec2zmS3sVit2Sp9o","ref":"Exod.14.2","text":"Speak unto the children of Israel, that they turn and encamp before Pihahiroth, between Migdol and the sea, over against Baalzephon: before it shall ye encamp by the sea.","year":-1491},{"id":"recsHdjH4ov9hveJq","ref":"Exod.14.3","text":"For Pharaoh will say of the children of Israel, They are entangled in the land, the wilderness hath shut them in.","year":-1491}]}
